properties.headline: Air Quality Alert issued February 1 at 4:25AM MST by NWS Rapid City SD
properties.description:
Southwest winds will continue to increase today, and remain gusty
through the afternoon. Wind speeds will be 25 to 30 mph, with gusts
to around 45 mph. Wind speeds will decrease some this evening, but
will remain breezy through the night.

The Wyoming Air Quality Division recommends the elderly, young
children, and individuals with respiratory problems avoid
excessive physical exertion and minimize outdoor activities during
this time. Although these people are most susceptible to health
impacts, the air quality division also advises that everyone
should avoid prolonged exposure to the poor air quality
conditions.

NWSheadline: BLOWING DUST HEALTH ALERT IN EFFECT FOR THE SOUTHERN POWDER RIVER BASIN OF NORTHEASTERN WYOMING FROM 11 AM THIS MORNING UNTIL 5 PM THIS AFTERNOON
